cards.name: Dalmatian Puppy - Tail Wagger
cards.cardText:
WHERE DID THEY ALL COME FROM? You may have up to 99 copies of Dalmatian Puppy - Tail Wagger in your deck.

First they steal your heart. Then they steal your chair.

cards.name: Baloo - von Bruinwald XIII
cards.cardText:
Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)
LET'S MAKE LIKE A TREE When this character is banished, gain 2 lore.

cards.name: Bernard - Brand-New Agent
cards.cardText:
I'LL CHECK IT OUT At the end of your turn, if this character is exerted, you may ready another chosen character of yours.

"You stay there. I'll look for scattered lore."

cards.name: Chernabog - Evildoer
cards.cardText:
THE POWER OF EVIL For each character card in your discard, you pay 1 {I} less to play this character.
SUMMON THE SPIRITS When you play this character, shuffle all character cards from your discard into your deck.

Darkness calls to minions everywhere.

cards.name: Joshua Sweet - The Doctor
cards.cardText:
Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)

"Heading out to the Inklands? Come on back if
you need patching up."

cards.name: Kida - Atlantean
cards.cardText: "Welcome to the Inklands"

cards.name: Kida - Protector of Atlantis
cards.cardText:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Kida.)
PERHAPS WE CAN SAVE OUR FUTURE When you play this character, all characters get -3 {S} until the start of your next turn.

"She has been chosen." —King Kashekim Nedakh

cards.name: Lucky - The 15th Puppy
cards.cardText:
GOOD AS NEW {E} — Reveal the top 3 cards of your deck. You may put each character card with cost 2 or less into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.
PUPPY LOVE Whenever this character quests, if you have 4 or more other characters in play, your other characters get +1 {L} this turn.

cards.name: Minnie Mouse - Musical Artist
cards.cardText:
Singer 3 (This character counts as cost 3 to sing songs.)
ENTOURAGE Whenever you play a character with Bodyguard, you may remove up to 2 damage from chosen character.

Her musical talents are off the charts!

cards.name: Miss Bianca - Rescue Aid Society Agent
cards.cardText:
Singer 4 (This character counts as cost 4 to sing songs.)

"Our society has never failed to answer a call for
help."
—Mr. Chairman

cards.name: Mr. Snoops - Inept Businessman
cards.cardText:
"This is simple, Snoops! I want that lore! The one
that shines like a diamond!"
—Madame Medusa

cards.name: Nani - Protective Sister
cards.cardText:
Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)

"Let me handle this, Lilo."

cards.name: Orville - Ace Pilot
cards.cardText:
"Boy, look at those things go! Whaddaya call 'em?
Inkrunners? I wish I could fly like that."

cards.name: Patch - Intimidating Pup
cards.cardText:
BARK {E} — Chosen character gets -2 {S} until the start of your next turn.

Just like Thunderbolt, he'll stand up to any bad guy.

cards.name: Perdita - Devoted Mother
cards.cardText:
COME ALONG, CHILDREN When you play this character and whenever she quests, you may play a character with cost 2 or less from your discard for free.

Her pups will follow her anywhere.

cards.name: Piglet - Pooh Pirate Captain
cards.cardText:
AND I'M THE CAPTAIN! While you have 2 or more other characters in play, this character gets +2 {L}.

"Ahoy! There's lore out there, and I'm g-gonna
find it!"

cards.name: Pluto - Determined Defender
cards.cardText:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Pluto.)
Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)
GUARD DOG At the start of your turn, remove up to 3 damage from this character.

cards.name: Pluto - Friendly Pooch
cards.cardText:
GOOD DOG {E} — You pay 1 {I} less for the next character you play this turn.

He just can't wait for new friends to arrive!

cards.name: Pongo - Determined Father
cards.cardText:
TWILIGHT BARK Once per turn, you may pay 2 {I} to reveal the top card of your deck. If it's a character card, put it into your hand. Otherwise, put it on the bottom of your deck.

"We'll find our way. I know we will!"

cards.name: Queen of Hearts - Wonderland Empress
cards.cardText:
ALL WAYS HERE ARE MY WAYS Whenever this character quests, your other Villain characters get +1 {L} this turn.

The more of the Inklands she claims, the more
she wants.

cards.name: Rolly - Hungry Pup
cards.cardText:
Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)

"I'm hungry, Mother. I really am."

cards.name: Tinker Bell - Generous Fairy
cards.cardText:
MAKE A NEW FRIEND When you play this character, look at the top 4 cards of your deck. You may reveal a character card and put it into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.

Plenty of berries—and friendship—to go around.

cards.name: Wendy Darling - Talented Sailor
cards.cardText:
With Tink's upgrades in place, Wendy took them to
the skies to find the missing mermaid.

cards.name: 99 Puppies
cards.cardText:
Whenever one of your characters quests this turn, gain 1 lore.

"Two, four, six, and three is nine, plus two is 11..."
—Roger

cards.name: Boss's Orders
cards.cardText:
Chosen character gains Support this turn. (Whenever they quest, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)

"Snoops! I know you can look harder! Find me that lore!"
—Madame Medusa

cards.name: Heal What Has Been Hurt
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 3 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Remove up to 3 damage from chosen character. Draw a card.

Let your power shine
Make the clock reverse...

cards.name: Quick Patch
cards.cardText:
Remove up to 3 damage from chosen location.

"Good as new! Well, almost."

cards.name: The Bare Necessities
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 2 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Chosen opponent reveals their hand and discards a non-character card of your choice.

Forget about your worries and your strife....

cards.name: Cleansing Rainwater
cards.cardText:
ANCIENT POWER Banish this item — Remove up to 2 damage from each of your characters.

Rainwater lands as stone melts and dragons fly again.

cards.name: Heart of Atlantis
cards.cardText:
LIFE GIVER {E} — You pay 2 {I} less for the next character you play this turn.

"It's what's keeping you—all of Atlantis—alive!"
—Milo Thatch

cards.name: Wildcat's Wrench
cards.cardText:
REBUILD {E} — Remove up to 2 damage from chosen location.

The right tool makes all the difference.

cards.name: Never Land - Mermaid Lagoon
cards.cardText:
The mermaids told Peter they'd seen some items floating by several days earlier,
but they were more concerned that one of their sisters had gone missing.

cards.name: Pride Lands - Pride Rock
cards.cardText:
WE ARE ALL CONNECTED Characters get +2 {W} while here.
LION HOME If you have a Prince or King character here, you pay 1 {I} less to play characters.

cards.name: Tiana's Palace - Jazz Restaurant
cards.cardText:
NIGHT OUT Characters can't be challenged while here.

In New Orleans, dreams can come true.

cards.name: Alice - Tea Alchemist
cards.cardText:
CURIOUSER AND CURIOUSER {E} — Exert chosen opposing character and all other opposing characters with the same name.

With the right tea leaves and a little magic, she
creates the perfect cup for any party guest.

cards.name: Chernabog's Followers - Creatures of Evil
cards.cardText:
RESTLESS SOULS Whenever this character quests, you may banish them to draw a card.

Let chaos reign.

cards.name: Diablo - Faithful Pet
cards.cardText:
LOOKING FOR AURORA Whenever you play a character named Maleficent, you may look at the top card of your deck. Put it on either the top or the bottom of your deck.

With a little ink-enhanced magic, nothing escapes
his sight.

cards.name: Genie - Supportive Friend
cards.cardText:
THREE WISHES Whenever this character quests, you may shuffle this card into your deck to draw 3 cards.

"Right here, direct from the lamp, right here for
your very much wish fulfillment."

cards.name: Hydros - Ice Titan
cards.cardText:
BLIZZARD {E} — Exert chosen character.

"Freeze Zeus!"

cards.name: Iago - Pretty Polly
cards.cardText:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)

"Your majesty certainly has a way with dumb
animals."
—Jafar

cards.name: Jafar - Lamp Thief
cards.cardText:
I AM YOUR MASTER NOW When you play this character, look at the top 2 cards of your deck. Put one on the top of your deck and the other on the bottom.

"I will rule as far as the eye can see."

cards.name: Jafar - Striking Illusionist
cards.cardText:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Jafar.)
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
POWER BEYOND MEASURE During your turn, while this character is exerted, whenever you draw a card, gain 1 lore.

cards.name: Lena Sabrewing - Rebellious Teenager
cards.cardText:
Rush (This character can challenge the turn they're played.)

Born from the shadows. Saved by friendship.

cards.name: Magic Broom - Dancing Duster
cards.cardText:
POWER CLEAN When you play this character, if you have a Sorcerer character in play, you may exert chosen opposing character. They can't ready at the start of their next turn.

Super-smooth tidiness.

cards.name: Magic Broom - Swift Cleaner
cards.cardText:
Rush (This character can challenge the turn they're played.)
CLEAN THIS, CLEAN THAT When you play this character, you may shuffle all Broom cards from your discard into your deck.

Super-speedy tidiness.

cards.name: Magic Broom - The Big Sweeper
cards.cardText:
CLEAN SWEEP While this character is at a location, it gets +2 {S}.

Super-sized tidiness.

cards.name: Magic Carpet - Flying Rug
cards.cardText:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
FIND THE WAY {E} — Move a character of yours to a location for free.

"Carpet and I can swoop in, grab the lore, and be back
before anyone knows it!" —Aladdin

cards.name: Magica De Spell - Ambitious Witch
Magica De Spell - The Midas Touch
cards.cardText:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Magica De Spell.)
ALL MINE Whenever this character quests, gain lore equal to the cost of one of your items in play.

"I can feel my powers growing the closer I get to
Scrooge's precious dime!"

cards.name: Magica De Spell - Thieving Sorceress
cards.cardText:
TELEKINESIS {E} — Return chosen item with cost equal to or less than this character's {S} to its player's hand.

"Do you know what I call this? A good start!"

cards.name: Maleficent - Mistress of All Evil
cards.cardText:
DARK KNOWLEDGE Whenever this character quests, you may draw a card.
DIVINATION During your turn, whenever you draw a card, you may move 1 damage counter from chosen character to chosen opposing character.

cards.name: Mama Odie - Voice of Wisdom
cards.cardText:
LISTEN TO YOUR MAMA NOW Whenever this character quests, you may move up to 2 damage counters from chosen character to chosen opposing character.

"That's the way to give it what it needs, Juju!"

cards.name: Pua - Potbellied Buddy
cards.cardText:
ALWAYS THERE When this character is banished, you may shuffle this card into your deck.

Always ready to lend a hand...er, snout.

cards.name: Rafiki - Mystical Fighter
cards.cardText:
Challenger +3 (While challenging, this character gets +3 {S}.)
ANCIENT SKILLS Whenever he challenges a Hyena character, this character takes no damage from the challenge.

Mind the stick!

cards.name: Stratos - Tornado Titan
cards.cardText:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
CYCLONE {E} — Gain lore equal to the number of Titan characters you have in play.

"Blow Zeus away!"

cards.name: The Firebird - Force of Destruction
cards.cardText:
It rages through the forest,
Wings spread wide with flame
Spring sings its ancient chorus
And green renews its claim

cards.name: The Queen - Hateful Rival
cards.cardText:
"A cobweb's strand to hold her fast
An eagle's eye to see her well
Sands of time to steal her past
Thus I cast my magic spell!"

cards.name: Treasure Guardian - Protector of the Cave
cards.cardText:
WHO DISTURBS MY SLUMBER? This character can't challenge or quest unless it is at a location.

"Only one may enter here."

cards.name: Ursula - Sea Witch
cards.cardText:
YOU'RE TOO LATE Whenever this character quests, chosen opposing character can't ready at the start of their next turn.

The secret contract has already been written.

cards.name: Bestow a Gift
cards.cardText:
Move 1 damage counter from chosen character to chosen opposing character.

"From magic ink I call this gift.
Fly my minion, thy wings be swift!"
—Maleficent

cards.name: It Calls Me
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 1 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Draw a card. Then, choose up to 3 cards from chosen opponent's discard and shuffle them into their deck.

I am everything I've learned and more

cards.name: Last-Ditch Effort
cards.cardText:
Exert chosen opposing character. Then chosen character of yours gains Challenger +2 this turn. (They get +2 {S} while challenging.)

"I got your back."

cards.name: The Boss is on a Roll
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 3 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Look at the top 5 cards of your deck. Put any number of them on the top or the bottom of your deck in any order. Gain 1 lore.

Go ahead! Make your choice!

cards.name: The Lamp
cards.cardText: GOOD OR EVIL Banish this item — If you have a character named Jafar in play, draw 2 cards. If you have a character named Genie in play, return chosen character with cost 4 or less to their player's hand.

cards.name: The Sorcerer's Hat
cards.cardText:
INCREDIBLE ENERGY {E}, 1 {I} — Name a card, then reveal the top card of your deck. If it's the named card, put that card into your hand. Otherwise, put it on the top of your deck.

Minnie approached it cautiously. Whoever had placed it here
might have prepared traps.

cards.name: Forbidden Mountain - Maleficent's Castle
cards.cardText:
An eerie quiet surrounds the castle—but beware of the dangerous
occupant within.

cards.name: The Queen's Castle - Mirror Chamber
cards.cardText:
USING THE MIRROR At the start of your turn, for each character you have here, you may draw a card.

Those who visit the mirror can choose their question—but not the answer.

cards.name: The Sorcerer's Tower - Wondrous Workspace
cards.cardText:
BROOM CLOSET Your characters named Magic Broom may move here for free.
MAGICAL POWER Characters get +1 {L} while here.

Everything you need to make some magic.

cards.name: Cubby - Mighty Lost Boy
cards.cardText:
THE BEAR Whenever this character moves to a location, he gets +3 {S} this turn.

With Peter holding off Hook, Cubby did what he
does best: break stuff.

cards.name: Cursed Merfolk - Ursula's Handiwork
cards.cardText:
POOR SOULS Whenever this character is challenged, each opponent chooses and discards a card.

"Now it's happened once or twice, someone couldn't
pay the price..."
—Ursula

cards.name: Don Karnage - Prince of Pirates
cards.cardText:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)

"You didn't expect to find me here, did you? Well
neither did I."

cards.name: Flotsam - Riffraff
cards.cardText:
EERIE PAIR Your characters named Jetsam get +3 {S}.

"Ursula needs lore to complete her plan...."

cards.name: Friar Tuck - Priest of Nottingham
cards.cardText:
YOU THIEVING SCOUNDREL When you play this character, the player or players with the most cards in their hand chooses and discards a card.

"Get outta my church! Out! Out! Out!"

cards.name: Helga Sinclair - Femme Fatale
cards.cardText:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Helga Sinclair.)
THIS CHANGES EVERYTHING Whenever this character quests, you may deal 3 damage to chosen damaged character.

cards.name: Helga Sinclair - Vengeful Partner
cards.cardText:
NOTHING PERSONAL When this character is challenged and banished, banish the challenging character.

"You said we were in this together!"

cards.name: Jetsam - Riffraff
cards.cardText:
Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)
EERIE PAIR Your characters named Flotsam gain Ward.

"There must be powerful lore here, very powerful."

cards.name: Kit Cloudkicker - Tough Guy
cards.cardText:
SKYSURFING When you play this character, you may return chosen opposing character with 2 {S} or less to their player's hand.

"It's been fun, guys, but I got to be going.
Yahoooo!"

cards.name: Lyle Tiberius Rourke - Cunning Mercenary
cards.cardText:
WELL, NOW YOU KNOW When you play this character, chosen opposing character gains Reckless during their next turn. (They can't quest and must challenge if able.)
THANKS FOR VOLUNTEERING Whenever one of your other characters is banished, each opponent loses 1 lore.

cards.name: Milo Thatch - Clever Cartographer
cards.cardText:
"Believe me, studying gibberish really can take
you places!"

cards.name: Milo Thatch - King of Atlantis
cards.cardText:
Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Milo Thatch.)
TAKE THEM BY SURPRISE When this character is banished, return all opposing characters to their players' hands.

"You don't know what you're tampering with."

cards.name: Morph - Space Goo
cards.cardText:
MIMICRY You may play any character with Shift on this character as if this character had any name.

"You jiggle-headed blob of mischief!"
—John Silver

cards.name: Peter Pan - Lost Boy Leader
cards.cardText:
I CAME TO LISTEN TO THE STORIES Once per turn, when this character moves to a location, gain lore equal to that location's {L}.

The Illumineers needed someone to find a missing
spellbook, and Peter was the first to volunteer.

cards.name: Prince John - Phony King
cards.cardText:
COLLECT TAXES Whenever this character quests, each opponent with more lore than you loses 2 lore.

"Too late to be known as John the First, he's sure to
be known as John the Worst!"
—Sheriff of Nottingham

cards.name: Robin Hood - Daydreamer
cards.cardText:
"Some days, it's nice to let the river do the
running."

cards.name: Shenzi - Hyena Pack Leader
cards.cardText:
I'LL HANDLE THIS While this character is at a location, she gets +3 {S}.
WHAT'S THE HURRY? While this character is at a location, whenever she challenges another character, you may draw a card.

"Why not stick around for dinner?"

cards.name: Sir Hiss - Aggravating Asp
cards.cardText:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)

Prince John isn't the only one collecting "taxes"

cards.name: Skippy - Energetic Rabbit
cards.cardText:
Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)

Even the bravest outlaw knows when to lie low.

cards.name: Starkey - Devious Pirate
cards.cardText: Point him in the right direction, and he'll do the rest.

cards.name: Stitch - Covert Agent
cards.cardText:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
HIDE While this character is at a location, he gains Ward. (Opponents can't choose them except to challenge.)

For such a flashy dresser, he sure is hard to spot.

cards.name: Ursula - Deceiver
cards.cardText: YOU'LL NEVER EVEN MISS IT When you play this character, chosen opponent reveals their hand and discards a song card of your choice.

cards.name: Ursula - Deceiver of All
cards.cardText:
WHAT A DEAL Whenever this character sings a song, you may play that song again from your discard for free, then put it on the bottom of your deck.

"I don't want much—just the most powerful lore!"

cards.name: Wildcat - Mechanic
cards.cardText:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
DISASSEMBLE {E} — Banish chosen item.

"I can take anything apart in under five minutes!"

cards.name: Zazu - Steward of the Pride Lands
cards.cardText:
IT'S TIME TO GO! While this character is at a location, he gets +1 {L}.

"I'd be lyin' if I said I ran the place, but welcome to
the Pride Lands all the same!"

cards.name: Has Set My Heaaaaaaart . . .
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 2 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Banish chosen item.

He's not real smart
And yet, he's touched my little cowhide heart

cards.name: I Will Find My Way
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 1 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Chosen character of yours gets +2 {S} this turn. They may move to a location for free.

I would go most anywhere
To feel like I belong

cards.name: Strike a Good Match
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 2 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Draw 2 cards, then choose and discard a card.

Please bring honor to us
Please bring honor to us all

cards.name: Airfoil
cards.cardText:
I GOT TO BE GOING {E} — If you've played 2 or more actions this turn, draw a card.

Discovered in the lost Sea Duck, it looked good as new.

cards.name: Robin's Bow
cards.cardText:
FOREST'S GIFT {E} — Deal 1 damage to chosen damaged character or location.
A BIT OF A LARK Whenever a character of yours named Robin Hood quests, you may ready this item.

"The forest always provides just what you need."
—Robin Hood

cards.name: Starlight Vial
cards.cardText:
EFFICIENT ENERGY {E} — You pay 2 {I} less for the next action you play this turn.
TRAP 2 {I}, Banish this item — Draw 2 cards, then choose and discard a card.

In the wrong hands, this vial of magic could be disastrous.

cards.name: De Vil Manor - Cruella's Estate
cards.cardText:
"They say the ol' place is haunted, or bewitched, or some such fiddle-faddle."
—Colonel

cards.name: Fang - River City
cards.cardText:
SURROUNDED BY WATER Characters gain Ward and Evasive while here. (Opponents can't choose them except to challenge. Only characters with Evasive can challenge them.)

A nation protected by fierce assassins and their even fiercer cats.

cards.name: Kuzco's Palace - Home of the Emperor
cards.cardText:
CITY WALLS Whenever a character is challenged and banished while here, banish the challenging character.

"Sure it's a little small, but also it DOESN'T HAVE A POOL!" —Kuzco

cards.name: Ariel - Adventurous Collector
cards.cardText:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
INSPIRING VOICE Whenever you play a song, chosen character of yours gains Evasive until the start of your next turn.

Shipwrecks are great places to find lore—and hide from sharks!

cards.name: Billy Bones - Keeper of the Map
cards.cardText:
"He's after me chest, that fiendish cyborg and his
band of cutthroats."

cards.name: Captain Hook - Master Swordsman
cards.cardText:
NEMESIS During your turn, whenever this character banishes another character in a challenge, ready this character. He can't quest for the rest of this turn.
MAN-TO-MAN Characters named Peter Pan lose Evasive and can't gain Evasive.

cards.name: Della Duck - Unstoppable Mom
cards.cardText:
Reckless (This character can't quest and must challenge each turn if able.)

"I survived the moon. How tough could the flooded
Inklands be?"

cards.name: HeiHei - Accidental Explorer
cards.cardText:
MINDLESS WANDERING Once per turn, when this character moves to a location, each opponent loses 1 lore.

Considering the coconut.

cards.name: Hydra - Deadly Serpent
cards.cardText:
WATCH THE TEETH Whenever this character is dealt damage, deal that much damage to chosen opposing character.

More heads are better than one.

cards.name: Jim Hawkins - Space Traveler
cards.cardText:
THIS IS IT! When you play this character, you may play a location with cost 4 or less for free.
TAKE THE HELM Whenever you play a location, this character may move there for free.

"You're gonna rattle the stars, you are."
—John Silver

cards.name: Jim Hawkins - Thrill Seeker
cards.cardText:
If you want a bigger reward, you've got to take
bigger risks.

cards.name: Kakamora - Menacing Sailor
cards.cardText:
PLUNDER When you play this character, each opponent loses 1 lore.

There's a bunch more where he came from.

cards.name: Madame Medusa - The Boss
cards.cardText:
THAT TERRIBLE WOMAN When you play this character, banish chosen opposing character with 3 {S} or less.

"Finding lore will be as easy as taking candy from
children."

cards.name: Maui - Soaring Demigod
cards.cardText:
Reckless (This character can't quest and must challenge each turn if able.)
IN MA BELLY Whenever a character of yours named HeiHei quests, this character gets +1 {L} and loses Reckless this turn.

"You got any more of those chickens hanging around?"

cards.name: Maui - Whale
cards.cardText:
THIS MISSION IS CURSED This character can't ready at the start of your turn.
I GOT YOUR BACK 2 {I} — Ready this character. He can't quest for the rest of this turn.

Always ready to make a splash.

cards.name: Milo Thatch - Spirited Scholar
cards.cardText:
I'M YOUR MAN! While this character is at a location, he gets +2 {S}.

"My grandpa never told me about this place!"

cards.name: Moana - Born Leader
cards.cardText:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Moana.)
WELCOME TO MY BOAT Whenever this character quests while at a location, ready all other characters here. They can't quest for the rest of this turn.

cards.name: Moana - Undeterred Voyager
cards.cardText:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)

No fire or storm will keep her from her goal.

cards.name: Nutsy - Vulture Henchman
cards.cardText:
"Nutsy, button your beak."
—Trigger

cards.name: Peter Pan - Never Land Hero
cards.cardText:
Rush (This character can challenge the turn they're played.)
OVER HERE, TINK While you have a character named Tinker Bell in play, this character gets +2 {S}.

With Peter, plans often meant diving headlong into
danger.

cards.name: Peter Pan - Pirate's Bane
cards.cardText:
Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Peter Pan.)
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
YOU'RE NEXT! Whenever he challenges a Pirate character, this character takes no damage from the challenge.

cards.name: Prince Eric - Expert Helmsman
cards.cardText:
SURPRISE MANEUVER When this character is banished, you may banish chosen character.

The storm came out of nowhere, forcing Eric
to turn back before he reached the mysterious
structure at the edge of Lorcana.

cards.name: Scroop - Backstabber
cards.cardText:
BRUTE While this character has damage, he gets +3 {S}.

Always keep him in front of you. And downwind,
if possible.

cards.name: Simba - Scrappy Cub
cards.cardText:
He'll join the hunt for lore after he's had a quick
snack.

cards.name: Slightly - Lost Boy
cards.cardText:
THE FOX If you have a character named Peter Pan in play, you pay 1 {I} less to play this character.
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)

"Pirates sure are easy to trick!"

cards.name: Stitch - Little Rocket
cards.cardText:
Rush (This character can challenge the turn they're played.)

"Who thought giving him power armor was a
good idea?!"
—Nani

cards.name: Trigger - Not-So-Sharp Shooter
cards.cardText:
OLD BETSY Your characters named Nutsy get +1 {L}.

"Criminently, Trigger! Point that peashooter the
other way."
—Sheriff of Nottingham

cards.name: Webby Vanderquack - Enthusiastic Duck
cards.cardText:
"Finding lore is a lot easier when you have a
grappling hook!"

cards.name: Divebomb
cards.cardText: Banish one of your characters with Reckless to banish chosen character with less {S} than that character.

cards.name: I've Got a Dream
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 2 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Ready chosen character of yours at a location. They can't quest for the rest of this turn. Gain lore equal to that location's {L}.

Tor would like to quit and be a florist
Gunther does interior design

cards.name: On Your Feet! Now!
cards.cardText:
Ready all your characters and deal 1 damage to each of them. They can't quest for the rest of this turn.

"Catch them! Before they get away!"

cards.name: Voyage
cards.cardText:
Move up to 2 characters of yours to the same location for free.

"We were voyagers! Why'd we stop?" —Moana

cards.name: Maui's Fish Hook
cards.cardText:
IT'S MAUI TIME! If you have a character named Maui in play, you may use this item's Shapeshift ability for free.
SHAPESHIFT {E}, 2 {I} — Choose one:
• Chosen character gains Evasive until the start of your next turn. (Only characters with Evasive can challenge them.)
• Chosen character gets +3 {S} this turn.

cards.name: Sumerian Talisman
cards.cardText:
SOURCE OF MAGIC During your turn, whenever one of your characters is banished in a challenge, you may draw a card.

"Summoned spirit from the dark
Show thyself before this arc."
—Lena Sabrewing

cards.name: Agrabah - Marketplace
cards.cardText:
"Welcome to Agrabah, city of mystery, of enchantment, and the finest
merchandise this side of the river."
—Merchant

cards.name: Jolly Roger - Hook's Ship
cards.cardText:
LOOK ALIVE, YOU SWABS! Characters gain Rush while here. (They can challenge the turn they're played.)
ALL HANDS ON DECK! Your Pirate characters may move here for free.

cards.name: RLS Legacy - Solar Galleon
cards.cardText:
THIS IS OUR SHIP Characters gain Evasive while here. (Only characters with Evasive can challenge them.)
HEAVE TOGETHER NOW If you have a character here, you pay 2 {I} less to move a character of yours here.

cards.name: Audrey Ramirez - The Engineer
cards.cardText:
Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)
SPARE PARTS Whenever this character quests, ready one of your items.

"How'd you break this thing, anyway?"

cards.name: Captain Amelia - First in Command
cards.cardText:
DISCIPLINE During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)

"I've spotted a strange structure on the horizon.
Hard to port, helmsman!"

cards.name: Dewey - Showy Nephew
cards.cardText:
Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)

"I got it! I knew I could do it! Dewey for the win!"

cards.name: Flintheart Glomgold - Lone Cheater
cards.cardText:
THEY'LL NEVER SEE IT COMING! During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)

"Nobody tells Flintheart Glomgold what to do!"

cards.name: Genie - Cramped in the Lamp
cards.cardText:
"Ten thousand years will give you such a crick in
the neck!"

cards.name: Gramma Tala - Keeper of Ancient Stories
cards.cardText:
THERE WAS ONLY OCEAN When you play this character, look at the top 2 cards of your deck. You may put one into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.

Listen with your whole heart, and the ancestors will
guide you.

cards.name: Gramma Tala - Spirit of the Ocean
cards.cardText:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Gramma Tala.)
DO YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE? Whenever a card is put into your inkwell, gain 1 lore.

She will always be with you, no matter how far your
journey takes you.

cards.name: Gyro Gearloose - Gadget Whiz
cards.cardText:
NOW TRY TO KEEP UP {E} — Put an item card from your discard on the top of your deck.

"Maybe the bulb tech will be less evil this time..."

cards.name: Huey - Savvy Nephew
cards.cardText:
Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)
THREE NEPHEWS Whenever this character quests, if you have characters named Dewey and Louie in play, you may draw 3 cards.

"This looks like part of a larger crystal!"

cards.name: King Louie - Bandleader
cards.cardText:
"Hold up, cuz. Why not sit back and enjoy some
sweet beats?"

cards.name: Kit Cloudkicker - Navigator
cards.cardText:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Kit Cloudkicker.)
Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)

cards.name: Kit Cloudkicker - Spunky Bear Cub
cards.cardText:
Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)

Thrilled to have his airfoil back, he launched into
the Inklands.

cards.name: Louie - Chill Nephew
cards.cardText:
Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)

"Found the last one!"

cards.name: Maid Marian - Delightful Dreamer
cards.cardText:
HIGHBORN LADY When you play this character, chosen character gets -2 {S} this turn.

She makes every space more beautiful.

cards.name: Mama Odie - Mystical Maven
cards.cardText:
THIS GOING TO BE GOOD Whenever you play a song, you may put the top card of your deck into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

"You dig a little deeper, you'll find everything you need."

cards.name: Pluto - Mickey's Clever Friend
cards.cardText:
Pluto's job was to keep Gustav's attention so
Minnie could get to the cave.

cards.name: Rufus - Orphanage Cat
cards.cardText:
TOO OLD TO BE CHASING MICE When this character is banished, you may put this card into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

"Faith is a bluebird you see from afar."

cards.name: Scrooge McDuck - Richest Duck in the World
cards.cardText:
I'M GOING HOME! During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)
I DIDN'T GET RICH BY BEING STUPID During your turn, whenever this character banishes another character in a challenge, you may play an item for free.

He can make money anywhere.

cards.name: Scrooge McDuck - Uncle Moneybags
cards.cardText:
TREASURE FINDER Whenever this character quests, you pay 1 {I} less for the next item you play this turn.

A strange new world is the perfect place to make a
strange new fortune!

cards.name: The Queen - Mirror Seeker
cards.cardText:
CALCULATING AND VAIN Whenever this character quests, you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck and put them back in any order.

She has only one question, and she'd better like
the answer.

cards.name: Tinker Bell - Very Clever Fairy
cards.cardText:
I CAN USE THAT Whenever one of your items is banished, you may put that card into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

She lives in a world of possibilities.

cards.name: Wendy Darling - Authority on Peter Pan
cards.cardText:
Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)
Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)

cards.name: Distract
cards.cardText: Chosen character gets -2 {S} this turn. Draw a card.

cards.name: Friend Like Me
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 5 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Each player puts the top 3 cards of their deck into their inkwell facedown and exerted.

You got some power in your corner now

cards.name: How Far I'll Go
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 4 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Look at the top 2 cards of your deck. Put one into your hand and the other into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

cards.name: Repair
cards.cardText:
Remove up to 3 damage from one of your locations or characters.

"I'm thinkin' about opening a shop here. What do you
think?"

cards.name: Aurelian Gyrosensor
cards.cardText:
SEEKING KNOWLEDGE Whenever one of your characters quests, you may look at the top card of your deck. Put it on either the top or the bottom of your deck.

"It can point you toward lost lore, but if you're not careful,
it'll lead you off a cliff."
—Venturo, an Illumineer

cards.name: Heart of Te Fiti
cards.cardText:
CREATE LIFE {E}, 2 {I} — Put the top card of your deck into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

It takes a pure heart to calm the raging storm within.

cards.name: Lucky Dime
cards.cardText:
NUMBER ONE {E}, 2 {I} — Choose a character of yours and gain lore equal to their {L}.

This one simple coin changed Scrooge's life forever.

cards.name: Scrooge's Top Hat
cards.cardText:
BUSINESS EXPERTISE {E} — You pay 1 {I} less for the next item you play this turn.

Just the thing to top off another brilliant deal.

cards.name: Vault Door
cards.cardText:
SEALED AWAY Your locations and characters at locations gain Resist +1. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)

Only Scrooge knows about this vault. And he's going to
keep it that way.

cards.name: Belle's House - Maurice's Workshop
cards.cardText:
LABORATORY If you have a character here, you pay 1 {I} less to play items.

Some of the most important tools in Lorcana are crafted here.

cards.name: McDuck Manor - Scrooge's Mansion
cards.cardText:
"It's only the coolest home in Lorcana!"
—Webby Vanderquack

cards.name: Motunui - Island Paradise
cards.cardText: REINCARNATION Whenever a character is banished while here, you may put that card into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

cards.name: Chief Tui - Proud of Motunui
cards.cardText: "Look at our home! There is no better place to be."

cards.name: Eeyore - Overstuffed Donkey
cards.cardText:
Resist +1 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 1.)

"Not much of a roadblock, but I suppose I'll do."

cards.name: Gustav the Giant - Terror of the Kingdom
cards.cardText:
ALL TIED UP This character enters play exerted and can't ready at the start of your turn.
BREAK FREE During your turn, whenever one of your other characters banishes another character in a challenge, you may ready this character.

cards.name: Hades - Hotheaded Ruler
cards.cardText:
CALL THE TITANS {E} — Ready your Titan characters.

"Brothers! Titans! Look at you in your squalid prison.
Who put you down there?"

cards.name: Helga Sinclair - Right-Hand Woman
cards.cardText:
Challenger +2 (While challenging, this character gets +2 {S}.)

"That was an order, not a suggestion. Let's go!"

cards.name: John Silver - Greedy Treasure Seeker
cards.cardText:
CHART YOUR OWN COURSE For each location you have in play, this character gains Resist +1 and gets +1 {L}. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)

"I was never much good at games. Always hated to lose."

cards.name: Kida - Royal Warrior
cards.cardText:
Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)

She's seen strange things before, but nothing like this.

cards.name: Little John - Resourceful Outlaw
cards.cardText:
Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Little John.)
OKAY, BIG SHOT While this character is exerted, your characters with Bodyguard gain Resist +1 and get +1 {L}. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)

cards.name: Little John - Robin's Pal
cards.cardText:
Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)
DISGUISED During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)

cards.name: Lythos - Rock Titan
cards.cardText:
Resist +2 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 2.)
STONE SKIN {E} — Chosen character gains Resist +2 this turn.

"Crush Zeus!"

cards.name: Mickey Mouse - Stalwart Explorer
cards.cardText:
LET'S TAKE A LOOK This character gets +1 {S} for each location you have in play.

Mickey knew just where to start searching for
the Sorcerer's Hat, but he didn't expect it to be
guarded.

cards.name: Mickey Mouse - Trumpeter
cards.cardText: SOUND THE CALL {E}, 2 {I} — Play a character for free.

cards.name: Minnie Mouse - Funky Spelunker
cards.cardText:
JOURNEY While this character is at a location, she gets +2 {S}.

She'll never cave under pressure.

cards.name: Mr. Smee - Bumbling Mate
cards.cardText:
OH DEAR, DEAR, DEAR At the end of your turn, if this character is exerted and you don't have a Captain character in play, deal 1 damage to this character.

"Catch those little—OUCH!"

cards.name: Mufasa - Champion of the Pride Lands
cards.cardText: Even his name makes enemies quiver in fear.

cards.name: Nala - Fierce Friend
cards.cardText: "Pinned ya again."

cards.name: Pyros - Lava Titan
cards.cardText:
ERUPTION During your turn, whenever this character banishes another character in a challenge, you may ready chosen character.

"Melt Zeus!"

cards.name: Razoul - Palace Guard
cards.cardText:
LOOKY HERE While this character has no damage, he gets +2 {S}.

"There's no princess here to save you this time,
street rat."

cards.name: Robin Hood - Beloved Outlaw
cards.cardText:
"You call this an ambush? Tsk, tsk. It's barely a
bushwhack."

cards.name: Robin Hood - Champion of Sherwood
cards.cardText:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Robin Hood.)
SKILLED COMBATANT During your turn, whenever this character banishes another character in a challenge, gain 2 lore.
THE GOOD OF OTHERS When this character is banished in a challenge, you may draw a card.

cards.name: Sheriff of Nottingham - Corrupt Official
cards.cardText:
TAXES SHOULD HURT Whenever you discard a card, you may deal 1 damage to chosen opposing character.

The thirteenth Rule of Villainy: Take everything you
can, but do it with a smile.

cards.name: Simba - Fighting Prince
cards.cardText:
STEP DOWN OR FIGHT When you play this character and whenever he banishes another character in a challenge during your turn, you may choose one: • Draw 2 cards, then choose and discard 2 cards. • Deal 2 damage to chosen character.

He's ready to restore the Pride Lands to their former glory.

cards.name: Simba - Rightful King
cards.cardText:
TRIUMPHANT STANCE During your turn, whenever this character banishes another character in a challenge, chosen opposing character can't challenge during their next turn.

With dangers multiplying all around, the pride needs
its guardian.

cards.name: Thaddeus E. Klang - Metallic Leader
cards.cardText:
MY TEETH ARE SHARPER Whenever this character quests while at a location, you may deal 1 damage to chosen character.

"Soon the bells will ring in the sound of your doom!"

cards.name: And Then Along Came Zeus
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 4 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Deal 5 damage to chosen character or location.

He hurled his thunderbolt—He zapped
Locked those suckers in a vault—They're trapped
And on his own stopped chaos in its tracks

cards.name: Ba-Boom!
cards.cardText:
Deal 2 damage to chosen character or location.

Bigger than your average boom!

cards.name: Olympus Would Be That Way
cards.cardText:
Your characters get +3 {S} while challenging a location this turn.

"Now that I set you free, what is the first thing you are
going to do?"
—Hades

cards.name: Rise of the Titans
cards.cardText:
Banish chosen location or item.

"Oh, we're in trouble, big trouble!"
—Hermes

cards.name: Captain Hook's Rapier
cards.cardText:
GET THOSE SCURVY BRATS! During your turn, whenever one of your characters banishes another character in a challenge, you may pay 1 {I} to draw a card.
LET'S HAVE AT IT! Your characters named Captain Hook gain Challenger +1. (They get +1 {S} while challenging.)

cards.name: Gizmosuit
cards.cardText:
CYBERNETIC ARMOR Banish this item — Chosen character gains Resist +2 until the start of your next turn. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 2.)

It stands in the Hall of Lorcana, waiting for someone to
speak the secret words.

cards.name: Map of Treasure Planet
cards.cardText:
KEY TO THE PORTAL {E} — You pay 1 {I} less for the next location you play this turn.
SHOW THE WAY You pay 1 {I} less to move your characters to a location.

"Gentlemen, this must be kept under lock and key."
—Captain Amelia

cards.name: Maui's Place of Exile - Hidden Island
cards.cardText:
ISOLATED Characters gain Resist +1 while here. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)

Nothing but boulders and sand—easy to miss.

cards.name: Nottingham - Prince John's Castle
cards.cardText:
Sir Hiss: "I say, sire, your mother's castle will be the perfect place to set up our scheme!"
Prince John: "Mommy!"

cards.name: The Bayou - Mysterious Swamp
cards.cardText:
SHOW ME THE WAY Whenever a character quests while here, you may draw a card, then choose and discard a card.

A place to find what you need, not just what you want.

cards.name: Chernabog - Evildoer
cards.cardText:
THE POWER OF EVIL For each character card in your discard, you pay 1 {I} less to play this character.
SUMMON THE SPIRITS When you play this character, shuffle all character cards from your discard into your deck.

cards.name: Kida - Protector of Atlantis
cards.cardText:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Kida.)
PERHAPS WE CAN SAVE OUR FUTURE When you play this character, all characters get -3 {S} until the start of your next turn.

cards.name: Pride Lands - Pride Rock
cards.cardText:
WE ARE ALL CONNECTED Characters get +2 {W} while here.
LION HOME If you have a Prince or King character here, you pay 1 {I} less to play characters.

cards.name: Jafar - Striking Illusionist
cards.cardText:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Jafar.)
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
POWER BEYOND MEASURE During your turn, while this character is exerted, whenever you draw a card, gain 1 lore.

cards.name: Maleficent - Mistress of All Evil
cards.cardText:
DARK KNOWLEDGE Whenever this character quests, you may draw a card.
DIVINATION During your turn, whenever you draw a card, you may move 1 damage counter from chosen character to chosen opposing character.

cards.name: The Sorcerer's Hat
cards.cardText: INCREDIBLE ENERGY {E}, 1 {I} — Name a card, then reveal the top card of your deck. If it's the named card, put that card into your hand. Otherwise, put it on the top of your deck.

cards.name: Morph - Space Goo
cards.cardText: MIMICRY You may play any character with Shift on this character as if this character had any name.

cards.name: Ursula - Deceiver of All
cards.cardText: WHAT A DEAL Whenever this character sings a song, you may play that song again from your discard for free, then put it on the bottom of your deck.

cards.name: Kuzco's Palace - Home of the Emperor
cards.cardText: CITY WALLS Whenever a character is challenged and banished while here, banish the challenging character.

cards.name: Captain Hook - Master Swordsman
cards.cardText:
NEMESIS During your turn, whenever this character banishes another character in a challenge, ready this character. He can't quest for the rest of this turn.
MAN-TO-MAN Characters named Peter Pan lose Evasive and can't gain Evasive.

cards.name: Peter Pan - Pirate's Bane
cards.cardText:
Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Peter Pan.)
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
YOU'RE NEXT! Whenever he challenges a Pirate character, this character takes no damage from the challenge.

cards.name: RLS Legacy - Solar Galleon
cards.cardText:
THIS IS OUR SHIP Characters gain Evasive while here. (Only characters with Evasive can challenge them.)
HEAVE TOGETHER NOW If you have a character here, you pay 2 {I} less to move a character of yours here.

cards.name: Gramma Tala - Spirit of the Ocean
cards.cardText:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Gramma Tala.)
DO YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE? Whenever a card is put into your inkwell, gain 1 lore.

cards.name: Scrooge McDuck - Richest Duck in the World
cards.cardText:
I'M GOING HOME! During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)
I DIDN'T GET RICH BY BEING STUPID During your turn, whenever this character banishes another character in a challenge, you may play an item for free.

cards.name: Belle's House - Maurice's Workshop
cards.cardText: LABORATORY If you have a character here, you pay 1 {I} less to play items.

cards.name: Mickey Mouse - Trumpeter
cards.cardText: SOUND THE CALL {E}, 2 {I} — Play a character for free.

cards.name: Robin Hood - Champion of Sherwood
cards.cardText:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Robin Hood.)
SKILLED COMBATANT During your turn, whenever this character banishes another character in a challenge, gain 2 lore.
THE GOOD OF OTHERS When this character is banished in a challenge, you may draw a card.

cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 4 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Deal 5 damage to chosen character or location.
